[src:1806-in-the-united-states/1727-in-great-britain] Events from the year **1727 in Great Britain**.
[src:1806-in-the-united-states/1750] Various sources, including the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, use the year 1750 as a baseline year for the end of the pre-industrial era.
[src:1806-in-the-united-states/1750] 1750 is commemorated as the year that started the Industrial Revolution, although the underpinnings of the Industrial Revolution could have started earlier.
[src:1806-in-the-united-states/1776-in-the-united-states] 1776 is celebrated in the United States as the official beginning of the nation, with the Declaration of Independence of the Thirteen Colonies from the British Empire issued on July 4.
